Schema Commons — Licensing
==========================

Schema Commons uses a dual-license model.

1. STANDARDS, SCHEMAS, AND DOCUMENTATION
   (everything except the /tools directory)
   ---------------------------------------------------------------
   Licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
   License (CC BY 4.0).

   You are free to:
     - Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format.
     - Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any
       purpose, even commercially.

   Under the following terms:
     - Attribution — You must give appropriate credit to "Schema Commons",
       provide a link to the license, and indicate if changes were made.

   Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
   Human-readable summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

   Suggested attribution:
     "Based on the <SC-0NN NAME vX.Y> standard by Schema Commons,
      licensed under CC BY 4.0."

2. REFERENCE TOOLING (the /tools directory)
   ---------------------------------------------------------------
